<P>
Ventura County Life; Part J; Page 7; Column 5 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
81 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATTITUDES ANTHONY SMITH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Age: 26 
</P>
<P>
Residence: Camarillo 
</P>
<P>
Occupation: Former electric guitarist with a struggling rock band called 
Decrepit Resurrection. 
</P>
<P>
Recently got a sales position with a Thousand Oaks art gallery. 
</P>
<P>
Outfit: Black pleated pants with a dark purple paisley shirt. 
</P>
<P>
Fashion attitude: "I grew up in rock concert T-shirts and basically lived in 
Birkenstocks and shorts. Then I got this job, and so my girlfriend took me 
shopping. I wanted stuff that was fashionable but still comfortable." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Smith and girlfriend Jennifer Skoblicki dress comfortably. MARILYN WEISS 
/ For The Times 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA122090-0036 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 324694 </DOCID>
