<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
SUIT OVER POLICE BUILDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city filed a $5-million lawsuit Monday against Kitchell CEM Inc. and Vanir 
Construction Management Inc. 
</P>
<P>
The two firms oversaw construction of the new $23.5-million police building, 
which was estimated to cost $17 million. The building was completed in June. 
The lawsuit blames the overruns on mismanagement by the two companies. 
</P>
<P>
The city hired construction litigation attorney Kenneth C. Gibbs of Gibbs, 
Giden, Locher &amp; Fleming to handle the suit. 
</P>
<P>
Officials of the construction firms could not be reached for comment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
