<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: MONROVIA; 
</P>
<P>
ALCOHOL PERMIT REJECTED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council on Tuesday turned down a request for an alcohol sales permit 
from a drive-through dairy located 600 feet from an elementary school. 
</P>
<P>
Bob's Dairy had been granted the permit by the city's Planning Commission, but 
that decision was appealed by the Monrovia School District, which opposed the 
permit because the dairy, at 448 W. Foothill Blvd., is in the neighborhood of 
Mayflower Elementary School. 
</P>
<P>
Councilwoman Mary Wilcox said she could not in good conscience approve the 
alcohol permit so close to a school. The council voted 4 to 1 to deny the 
permit, with Mayor Robert Bartlett dissenting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
