SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ARCADIA; 
</P>
<P>
45-DAY BAN ON HILL BUILDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council adopted a 45-day moratorium on construction on undeveloped 
hillsides. 
</P>
<P>
Unanimously approved Tuesday, the moratorium is effective immediately. The 
restricted area includes undeveloped land bounded on the south by Elkins Avenue 
and on the north, west and east by the city boundary. 
</P>
<P>
During the 45 days, the Planning Department will develop specific guidelines on 
hillside development, said assistant planner Donna Butler. 
</P>
