<HEADLINE>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
UNBEATEN ESTANCIA WINS BOLSA GRANDE TOURNAMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
GARDEN GROVE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Estancia High School girls' basketball team ran its unbeaten streak to nine 
games, defeating Trabuco Hills, 73-48, in the finals of the Bolsa Grande 
Tournament Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
The Eagles took a 36-19 halftime lead on the shooting of Melody Earle, the 
tournament's Most Valuable Player, and forwards Patrice Lumpkin and Monique 
Sweet. 
</P>
<P>
Estancia led, 56-29, late in the third quarter before Trabuco Hills made a 10-0 
run, but the Eagles went on their own 14-0 run early in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Lumpkin has 21 points, Earle 20 and Sweet 18. Estancia shot 44.7% from the 
field and its man-to-man defense held Trabuco Hills (5-3) to 39.2%. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
In other Bolsa Grande tournament games: 
</P>
<P>
Capistrano Valley 49, Bolsa Grande 39 -- Angie White had 18 points for 
Capistrano Valley (6-2) in the third-place game. Judy Valenzuela had 15 for 
Bolsa Grande (4-4). 
</P>
<P>
Newport Harbor 77, Laguna Hills 38 -- Center Maureen McLaren had 20 points for 
Newport Harbor (4-5) in a consolation game. FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ 
</P>
