WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
</P>
<P>
NO RING AROUND THE COLLAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In a unanimous vote, the City Council last week directed city staff to study 
the feasibility of requiring new office buildings to include showers and 
lockers to encourage workers to ride bicycles to work. 
</P>
<P>
"I would bicycle to work every day if I knew I didn't have to get sweat on my 
shirt and collar," said Councilman Dennis Zane, who introduced the study 
proposal. 
</P>
<P>
The staff was asked to consider whether city-sponsored regional shower and 
locker facilities are good ideas because some businesses would be too small to 
afford their own facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
