<P>
TOLAND DUMP WILL BE CLOSED SATURDAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JANET BERGAMO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Toland Road Landfill between Santa Paula and Fillmore will be closed 
Saturdays beginning Feb. 1, and a program for recycling household hazardous 
wastes at the site will be changed to another day, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The Ventura Regional Sanitation District, which operates the Toland Road site 
and the Bailard landfill in Oxnard, is expected to take final action on the 
closure today. 
</P>
<P>
John Conaway, the district's solid waste manager, said the landfill has been 
operating from 7:30 a.m. until 4:30 p.m. Tuesday through Saturday. The district 
is changing the schedule to Monday through Friday because Saturday revenues did 
not offset the cost of running the dump, he said. 
</P>
<P>
"We have to maximize the amount we can get during five days. We're hoping 
Monday will be the better business day," Conaway said. JANET BERGAMO 
</P>
