<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF : HAYDEN SAYS HE WILL HEAD ASSEMBLY 
EDUCATION PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Assemblyman Tom Hayden (D-Santa Monica) said on Wednesday that when the 
Legislature reconvenes next month, he will become the chairman of a new 
Assembly Higher Education Committee. As a result, Hayden will give up the 
chairmanship of the Assembly Labor and Employment Committee. 
</P>
<P>
A spokesman for Assembly Speaker Willie Brown (D-San Francisco) would not 
comment on Hayden's announcement. Brown is expected to announce new committee 
assignments next month. 
</P>
<P>
The apparent committee switch comes amid reports that Brown is being pressured 
to strip Hayden of the labor post as punishment for several supposed political 
sins. These include his championing of "Big Green," the sweeping environmental 
initiative voters rejected last month. Hayden dismissed suggestions that he was 
being punished, but acknowledged that his "Big Green" leadership role "may have 
ruffled some feathers" in the Legislature. 
</P>
</TEXT>
