<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST: WHITTIER; 
</P>
<P>
RIO HONDO PRESIDENT GETS 2-YEAR CONTRACT EXTENSION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rio Hondo Community College President Alex Sanchez has received a vote of 
confidence from the board of trustees who unanimously agreed to give him a 
two-year extension on his three-year contract. 
</P>
<P>
In July, 1989, trustees voted 3 to 2 to hire Sanchez. 
</P>
<P>
Board members Bill Hernandez and Ralph Pacheco voted for another candidate. 
</P>
<P>
However, Hernandez and Pacheco said Sanchez has done a good job since replacing 
Herbert M. Sussman, who had been president since 1982. 
</P>
<P>
"This represents a vote of confidence. This gives him an opportunity to 
implement his goals," Pacheco said. 
</P>
<P>
Hernandez said also that Sanchez had done a good job in helping bring harmony 
to the board whose members who had often been at political odds with one 
another. 
</P>
<P>
The new contract does not call for any increase in pay for Sanchez, who was 
hired at $91,875 a year. However, he has received two cost-of-living increases, 
a 3.3% and a 5% hike. 
</P>
<P>
Sanchez is the college's first Latino top administrator. More than half of the 
school's 12,600 students are Latino. 
</P>
<P>
Sanchez was a vice president of the University of New Mexico before taking the 
Rio Hondo job. 
</P>
</TEXT>
