<P>
264 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
RUSH LEADS VALLEY TO TITLE, 71-65 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tisa Rush scored 28 points, handed out six assists and had six steals as the 
Valley College women's basketball team stormed to the Riverside tournament 
championship with a 71-65 victory over Riverside City College on Wednesday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
Rush was named the tournament's most valuable player. 
</P>
<P>
Claudia Rocha added 15 points for Valley (13-1) and was selected to the 
all-tournament team. Roz Linton grabbed 15 rebounds for the winners. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
