Robert M. Kreek, president of Fox Cable Programming, has been named president 
and chief executive of Comedy TV, the new cable-TV comedy channel owned jointly 
by Time Warner Inc. and Viacom International. 
</P>
<P>
The creation of Comedy TV, which was formed by the merger of Time Warner's 
Comedy Channel and Viacom's Ha! cable network, was announced Tuesday. Kreek, a 
former president of Fox Television Stations, will report to an eight-member 
board composed of an equal number of representatives from the parent companies. 
He will relocate to New York from Los Angeles. 
</P>
