<TEXT>
<P>
MONKEY BUSINESS: The Santa Ana Zoo isn't happy to have this monkey off its 
back. The zoo has decided to say goodby to two very rare primates -- red-backed 
squirrel monkeys -- and send them to Phoenix. . . . There, the two monkeys will 
join a third friend recently captured, so the Phoenix Zoo can start the 
nation's first captive-breeding program for the monkeys. Santa Ana Zoo 
officials say it's their small way of helping out a species that has almost 
vanished from the world. Jon Nalick and Mark Landsbaum 
</P>
