<TEXT>
<P>
In this column (Legal View) two weeks ago, it was incorrectly reported that to 
use the method of substituted service in small claims court, a plaintiff must 
first use "due diligence" in trying to personally serve a defendant. In fact, 
in small claims court, the substituted service method described in the column 
may be used without first attempting personal service. See Code of Civil 
Procedure section 116.3. 
</P>
